subject: p19765968
History: -year-old male with myeloma, with shortness of breath.
Findings: A mild diffuse interstitial abnormality persists, possibly reflecting known airways abnormalities previously imaged by CT. There are no new focal opacities. No effusion and no pneumothorax. The hilar and cardiomediastinal contours are unchanged. There is no pulmonary vascular congestion or pulmonary edema. Chronic deformity of the distal right clavicle is unchanged from prior studies. There is mild compression deformity of two mid-thoracic vertebral bodies, similarly stable. No new fractures are identified.
Impression: Little change in diffuse interstitial prominence, without new focal parenchymal opacity. Chronic osseous changes involving the distal right clavicle and mid-thoracic vertebral bodies are again noted.
